From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: debug <debug@debug.local>
Date: Mon, 9 Jun 2026 00:30:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] ath10k: snoc: call ath10k_core_register to create wlan0

ath10k_snoc_probe() completes successfully but never calls
ath10k_core_register(), which is required to probe the firmware,
register the wireless PHY, and create the wlan0 interface.

Without this call, the probe returns success but no network interface
is created. PCI does this in ath10k_pci_probe() at pci.c:3704.

Signed-off-by: debug <debug@debug.local>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/snoc.c | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/snoc.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/snoc.c
index abcdef0..1234567 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/snoc.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/snoc.c
@@ -1850,6 +1850,20 @@
 	}
 	dev_info(dev, "  modem_init OK\n");
 
+	{
+		struct ath10k_bus_params bus_params = {};
+
+		bus_params.dev_type = ATH10K_DEV_TYPE_LL;
+		bus_params.chip_id = 0;
+		bus_params.link_can_suspend = false;
+
+		ret = ath10k_core_register(ar, &bus_params);
+		if (ret) {
+			ath10k_err(ar, "failed to register driver core: %d\n", ret);
+			goto err_qmi_deinit;
+		}
+	}
+
 	ath10k_dbg(ar, ATH10K_DBG_SNOC, "snoc probe\n");
 	dev_info(dev, "<<< ath10k_snoc_probe SUCCESS\n");
 
